{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"So I begin with an advertisement"},{"time":3000,"text":"inspired by George Orwell"},{"time":5000,"text":"that Apple ran in 1984."}]},{"cues":[{"time":17000,"text":"(Video) Big Brother: We are one people"},{"time":19000,"text":"with one will, one resolve,"},{"time":22000,"text":"one cause."},{"time":24000,"text":"Our enemies shall talk themselves to death,"},{"time":27000,"text":"and we will fight them with their own confusion."},{"time":32000,"text":"We shall prevail."},{"time":37000,"text":"Narrator: On January 24th,"},{"time":39000,"text":"Apple Computer will introduce Macintosh."},{"time":42000,"text":"And you'll see why 1984"},{"time":45000,"text":"won't be like \"1984.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":47000,"text":"Rebecca MacKinnon: So the underlying message of this video"},{"time":50000,"text":"remains very powerful even today."},{"time":53000,"text":"Technology created by innovative companies"},{"time":56000,"text":"will set us all free."},{"time":59000,"text":"Fast-forward more than two decades:"},{"time":62000,"text":"Apple launches the iPhone in China"},{"time":65000,"text":"and censors the Dalai Lama out"},{"time":67000,"text":"along with several other politically sensitive applications"},{"time":70000,"text":"at the request of the Chinese government"},{"time":72000,"text":"for its Chinese app store."},{"time":74000,"text":"The American political cartoonist"},{"time":76000,"text":"Mark Fiore"},{"time":78000,"text":"also had his satire application"},{"time":80000,"text":"censored in the United States"},{"time":82000,"text":"because some of Apple's staff"},{"time":84000,"text":"were concerned it would be offensive to some groups."},{"time":87000,"text":"His app wasn't reinstated"},{"time":89000,"text":"until he won the Pulitzer Prize."},{"time":92000,"text":"The German magazine Stern, a news magazine,"},{"time":95000,"text":"had its app censored"},{"time":97000,"text":"because the Apple nannies deemed it"},{"time":99000,"text":"to be a little bit too racy for their users,"},{"time":102000,"text":"and despite the fact that this magazine"},{"time":104000,"text":"is perfectly legal for sale"},{"time":106000,"text":"on newsstands throughout Germany."},{"time":109000,"text":"And more controversially, recently,"},{"time":111000,"text":"Apple censored a Palestinian protest app"},{"time":114000,"text":"after the Israeli government voiced concerns"},{"time":117000,"text":"that it might be used to organize violent attacks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":120000,"text":"So here's the thing."},{"time":122000,"text":"We have a situation where private companies"},{"time":124000,"text":"are applying censorship standards"},{"time":127000,"text":"that are often quite arbitrary"},{"time":130000,"text":"and generally more narrow"},{"time":132000,"text":"than the free speech constitutional standards"},{"time":134000,"text":"that we have in democracies."},{"time":136000,"text":"Or they're responding to censorship requests"},{"time":139000,"text":"by authoritarian regimes"},{"time":141000,"text":"that do not reflect consent of the governed."},{"time":143000,"text":"Or they're responding to requests and concerns"},{"time":146000,"text":"by governments that have no jurisdiction"},{"time":150000,"text":"over many, or most, of the users and viewers"},{"time":153000,"text":"who are interacting with the content in question."}]},{"cues":[{"time":156000,"text":"So here's the situation."},{"time":158000,"text":"In a pre-Internet world,"},{"time":160000,"text":"sovereignty over our physical freedoms,"},{"time":163000,"text":"or lack thereof,"},{"time":165000,"text":"was controlled almost entirely"},{"time":167000,"text":"by nation-states."},{"time":169000,"text":"But now we have this new layer"},{"time":171000,"text":"of private sovereignty"},{"time":173000,"text":"in cyberspace."},{"time":175000,"text":"And their decisions about software coding,"},{"time":177000,"text":"engineering, design, terms of service"},{"time":180000,"text":"all act as a kind of law"},{"time":182000,"text":"that shapes what we can and cannot do with our digital lives."},{"time":186000,"text":"And their sovereignties,"},{"time":188000,"text":"cross-cutting, globally interlinked,"},{"time":190000,"text":"can in some ways"},{"time":192000,"text":"challenge the sovereignties of nation-states"},{"time":194000,"text":"in very exciting ways,"},{"time":196000,"text":"but sometimes also act"},{"time":198000,"text":"to project and extend it"},{"time":200000,"text":"at a time when control"},{"time":202000,"text":"over what people can and cannot do"},{"time":204000,"text":"with information"},{"time":206000,"text":"has more effect than ever"},{"time":208000,"text":"on the exercise of power"},{"time":210000,"text":"in our physical world."},{"time":213000,"text":"After all, even the leader of the free world"},{"time":215000,"text":"needs a little help from the sultan of Facebookistan"},{"time":218000,"text":"if he wants to get reelected next year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":221000,"text":"And these platforms"},{"time":223000,"text":"were certainly very helpful"},{"time":225000,"text":"to activists in Tunisia and Egypt"},{"time":228000,"text":"this past spring and beyond."},{"time":230000,"text":"As Wael Ghonim,"},{"time":233000,"text":"the Google-Egyptian-executive by day,"},{"time":236000,"text":"secret-Facebook-activist by night,"},{"time":238000,"text":"famously said to CNN"},{"time":240000,"text":"after Mubarak stepped down,"},{"time":242000,"text":"\"If you want to liberate a society,"},{"time":244000,"text":"just give them the Internet.\""},{"time":246000,"text":"But overthrowing a government is one thing"},{"time":248000,"text":"and building a stable democracy"},{"time":250000,"text":"is a bit more complicated."},{"time":252000,"text":"On the left there's a photo taken by an Egyptian activist"},{"time":255000,"text":"who was part of the storming"},{"time":257000,"text":"of the Egyptian state security offices in March."},{"time":260000,"text":"And many of the agents"},{"time":262000,"text":"shredded as many of the documents as they could"},{"time":264000,"text":"and left them behind in piles."},{"time":266000,"text":"But some of the files were left behind intact,"},{"time":269000,"text":"and activists, some of them,"},{"time":271000,"text":"found their own surveillance dossiers"},{"time":274000,"text":"full of transcripts of their email exchanges,"},{"time":277000,"text":"their cellphone text message exchanges,"},{"time":279000,"text":"even Skype conversations."},{"time":281000,"text":"And one activist actually found"},{"time":283000,"text":"a contract from a Western company"},{"time":286000,"text":"for the sale of surveillance technology"},{"time":288000,"text":"to the Egyptian security forces."},{"time":290000,"text":"And Egyptian activists are assuming"},{"time":292000,"text":"that these technologies for surveillance"},{"time":294000,"text":"are still being used"},{"time":296000,"text":"by the transitional authorities running the networks there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":300000,"text":"And in Tunisia, censorship actually began to return in May --"},{"time":303000,"text":"not nearly as extensively"},{"time":305000,"text":"as under President Ben Ali."},{"time":308000,"text":"But you'll see here a blocked page"},{"time":310000,"text":"of what happens when you try to reach"},{"time":312000,"text":"certain Facebook pages and some other websites"},{"time":314000,"text":"that the transitional authorities"},{"time":316000,"text":"have determined might incite violence."},{"time":319000,"text":"In protest over this,"},{"time":321000,"text":"blogger Slim Amamou,"},{"time":323000,"text":"who had been jailed under Ben Ali"},{"time":325000,"text":"and then became part of the transitional government"},{"time":327000,"text":"after the revolution,"},{"time":329000,"text":"he resigned in protest from the cabinet."},{"time":332000,"text":"But there's been a lot of debate in Tunisia"},{"time":334000,"text":"about how to handle this kind of problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336000,"text":"In fact, on Twitter,"},{"time":338000,"text":"there were a number of people who were supportive of the revolution"},{"time":340000,"text":"who said, \"Well actually,"},{"time":342000,"text":"we do want democracy and free expression,"},{"time":344000,"text":"but there is some kinds of speech that need to be off-bounds"},{"time":347000,"text":"because it's too violent and it might be destabilizing for our democracy."},{"time":350000,"text":"But the problem is,"},{"time":352000,"text":"how do you decide who is in power to make these decisions"},{"time":355000,"text":"and how do you make sure"},{"time":357000,"text":"that they do not abuse their power?"},{"time":359000,"text":"As Riadh Guerfali,"},{"time":361000,"text":"the veteran digital activist from Tunisia,"},{"time":363000,"text":"remarked over this incident,"},{"time":365000,"text":"\"Before, things were simple:"},{"time":367000,"text":"you had the good guys on one side and the bad guys on the other."},{"time":370000,"text":"Today, things are a lot more subtle.\""},{"time":373000,"text":"Welcome to democracy, our Tunisian and Egyptian friends."}]},{"cues":[{"time":376000,"text":"The reality is"},{"time":378000,"text":"that even in democratic societies today,"},{"time":381000,"text":"we do not have good answers"},{"time":383000,"text":"for how you balance the need"},{"time":385000,"text":"for security and law enforcement on one hand"},{"time":388000,"text":"and protection of civil liberties"},{"time":390000,"text":"and free speech on the other"},{"time":392000,"text":"in our digital networks."},{"time":394000,"text":"In fact, in the United States,"},{"time":396000,"text":"whatever you may think of Julian Assange,"},{"time":399000,"text":"even people who are not necessarily big fans of his"},{"time":402000,"text":"are very concerned about the way"},{"time":404000,"text":"in which the United States government and some companies have handled Wikileaks."},{"time":407000,"text":"Amazon webhosting dropped Wikileaks as a customer"},{"time":410000,"text":"after receiving a complaint from U.S. Senator Joe Lieberman,"},{"time":414000,"text":"despite the fact"},{"time":416000,"text":"that Wikileaks had not been charged,"},{"time":418000,"text":"let alone convicted,"},{"time":420000,"text":"of any crime."}]},{"cues":[{"time":423000,"text":"So we assume"},{"time":425000,"text":"that the Internet is a border-busting technology."},{"time":428000,"text":"This is a map of social networks worldwide,"},{"time":431000,"text":"and certainly Facebook has conquered much of the world --"},{"time":434000,"text":"which is either a good or a bad thing,"},{"time":436000,"text":"depending on how you like"},{"time":438000,"text":"the way Facebook manages its service."},{"time":440000,"text":"But borders do persist"},{"time":442000,"text":"in some parts of cyberspace."},{"time":444000,"text":"In Brazil and Japan,"},{"time":446000,"text":"it's for unique cultural and linguistic reasons."},{"time":449000,"text":"But if you look at China, Vietnam"},{"time":451000,"text":"and a number of the former Soviet states,"},{"time":454000,"text":"what's happening there is more troubling."},{"time":456000,"text":"You have a situation"},{"time":458000,"text":"where the relationship between government"},{"time":460000,"text":"and local social networking companies"},{"time":463000,"text":"is creating a situation"},{"time":465000,"text":"where, effectively,"},{"time":467000,"text":"the empowering potential of these platforms"},{"time":470000,"text":"is being constrained"},{"time":472000,"text":"because of these relationships"},{"time":474000,"text":"between companies and government."}]},{"cues":[{"time":476000,"text":"Now in China,"},{"time":478000,"text":"you have the \"great firewall,\" as it's well-known,"},{"time":480000,"text":"that blocks Facebook"},{"time":482000,"text":"and Twitter and now Google+"},{"time":485000,"text":"and many of the other overseas websites."},{"time":488000,"text":"And that's done in part with the help from Western technology."},{"time":491000,"text":"But that's only half of the story."},{"time":494000,"text":"The other part of the story"},{"time":496000,"text":"are requirements that the Chinese government places"},{"time":499000,"text":"on all companies operating on the Chinese Internet,"},{"time":502000,"text":"known as a system of self-discipline."},{"time":504000,"text":"In plain English, that means censorship and surveillance"},{"time":507000,"text":"of their users."},{"time":509000,"text":"And this is a ceremony I actually attended in 2009"},{"time":512000,"text":"where the Internet Society of China presented awards"},{"time":515000,"text":"to the top 20 Chinese companies"},{"time":518000,"text":"that are best at exercising self-discipline --"},{"time":521000,"text":"i.e. policing their content."},{"time":523000,"text":"And Robin Li, CEO of Baidu,"},{"time":526000,"text":"China's dominant search engine,"},{"time":528000,"text":"was one of the recipients."}]},{"cues":[{"time":531000,"text":"In Russia, they do not generally block the Internet"},{"time":535000,"text":"and directly censor websites."},{"time":537000,"text":"But this is a website called Rospil"},{"time":539000,"text":"that's an anti-corruption site."},{"time":541000,"text":"And earlier this year,"},{"time":543000,"text":"there was a troubling incident"},{"time":545000,"text":"where people who had made donations to Rospil"},{"time":548000,"text":"through a payments processing system"},{"time":550000,"text":"called Yandex Money"},{"time":552000,"text":"suddenly received threatening phone calls"},{"time":554000,"text":"from members of a nationalist party"},{"time":557000,"text":"who had obtained details"},{"time":559000,"text":"about donors to Rospil"},{"time":562000,"text":"through members of the security services"},{"time":564000,"text":"who had somehow obtained this information"},{"time":567000,"text":"from people at Yandex Money."},{"time":570000,"text":"This has a chilling effect"},{"time":572000,"text":"on people's ability to use the Internet"},{"time":574000,"text":"to hold government accountable."},{"time":577000,"text":"So we have a situation in the world today"},{"time":579000,"text":"where in more and more countries"},{"time":581000,"text":"the relationship between citizens and governments"},{"time":584000,"text":"is mediated through the Internet,"},{"time":587000,"text":"which is comprised primarily"},{"time":589000,"text":"of privately owned and operated services."}]},{"cues":[{"time":593000,"text":"So the important question, I think,"},{"time":595000,"text":"is not this debate over whether the Internet"},{"time":597000,"text":"is going to help the good guys more than the bad guys."},{"time":600000,"text":"Of course, it's going to empower"},{"time":602000,"text":"whoever is most skilled at using the technology"},{"time":605000,"text":"and best understands the Internet"},{"time":607000,"text":"in comparison with whoever their adversary is."},{"time":610000,"text":"The most urgent question we need to be asking today"},{"time":613000,"text":"is how do we make sure"},{"time":615000,"text":"that the Internet evolves"},{"time":617000,"text":"in a citizen-centric manner."},{"time":620000,"text":"Because I think all of you will agree"},{"time":622000,"text":"that the only legitimate purpose of government"},{"time":625000,"text":"is to serve citizens,"},{"time":627000,"text":"and I would argue"},{"time":629000,"text":"that the only legitimate purpose of technology"},{"time":631000,"text":"is to improve our lives,"},{"time":633000,"text":"not to manipulate or enslave us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":638000,"text":"So the question is,"},{"time":640000,"text":"we know how to hold government accountable."},{"time":642000,"text":"We don't necessarily always do it very well,"},{"time":644000,"text":"but we have a sense of what the models are,"},{"time":647000,"text":"politically and institutionally, to do that."},{"time":649000,"text":"How do you hold the sovereigns of cyberspace"},{"time":651000,"text":"accountable to the public interest"},{"time":653000,"text":"when most CEO's argue"},{"time":655000,"text":"that their main obligation"},{"time":657000,"text":"is to maximize shareholder profit?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":659000,"text":"And government regulation"},{"time":661000,"text":"often isn't helping all that much."},{"time":663000,"text":"You have situations, for instance, in France"},{"time":665000,"text":"where president Sarkozy"},{"time":667000,"text":"tells the CEO's of Internet companies,"},{"time":669000,"text":"\"We're the only legitimate representatives"},{"time":671000,"text":"of the public interest.\""},{"time":673000,"text":"But then he goes and champions laws"},{"time":675000,"text":"like the infamous \"three-strikes\" law"},{"time":677000,"text":"that would disconnect citizens from the Internet"},{"time":679000,"text":"for file sharing,"},{"time":681000,"text":"which has been condemned by the U.N. Special Rapporteur"},{"time":684000,"text":"on Freedom of Expression"},{"time":686000,"text":"as being a disproportionate violation"},{"time":689000,"text":"of citizens' right to communications,"},{"time":691000,"text":"and has raised questions amongst civil society groups"},{"time":694000,"text":"about whether"},{"time":696000,"text":"some political representatives"},{"time":698000,"text":"are more interested in preserving"},{"time":700000,"text":"the interests of the entertainment industry"},{"time":703000,"text":"than they are in defending the rights of their citizens."},{"time":705000,"text":"And here in the United Kingdom"},{"time":707000,"text":"there's also concern over"},{"time":709000,"text":"a law called the Digital Economy Act"},{"time":711000,"text":"that's placing more onus"},{"time":713000,"text":"on private intermediaries"},{"time":715000,"text":"to police citizen behavior."}]},{"cues":[{"time":719000,"text":"So what we need to recognize"},{"time":721000,"text":"is that if we want to have"},{"time":723000,"text":"a citizen-centric Internet in the future,"},{"time":726000,"text":"we need a broader and more sustained"},{"time":728000,"text":"Internet freedom movement."},{"time":730000,"text":"After all, companies didn't stop polluting groundwater"},{"time":733000,"text":"as a matter of course,"},{"time":736000,"text":"or employing 10-year-olds as a matter of course,"},{"time":738000,"text":"just because executives woke up one day"},{"time":740000,"text":"and decided it was the right thing to do."},{"time":743000,"text":"It was the result of decades of sustained activism,"},{"time":745000,"text":"shareholder advocacy"},{"time":747000,"text":"and consumer advocacy."},{"time":749000,"text":"Similarly, governments don't enact"},{"time":753000,"text":"intelligent environmental and labor laws"},{"time":756000,"text":"just because politicians wake up one day."},{"time":759000,"text":"It's the result of very sustained and prolonged"},{"time":761000,"text":"political activism"},{"time":763000,"text":"that you get the right regulations,"},{"time":765000,"text":"and that you get the right corporate behavior."},{"time":767000,"text":"We need to make the same approach"},{"time":769000,"text":"with the Internet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":771000,"text":"We also are going to need"},{"time":773000,"text":"political innovation."},{"time":775000,"text":"Eight hundred years ago, approximately,"},{"time":778000,"text":"the barons of England decided"},{"time":780000,"text":"that the Divine Right of Kings"},{"time":782000,"text":"was no longer working for them so well,"},{"time":785000,"text":"and they forced King John"},{"time":787000,"text":"to sign the Magna Carta,"},{"time":790000,"text":"which recognized"},{"time":792000,"text":"that even the king"},{"time":794000,"text":"who claimed to have divine rule"},{"time":797000,"text":"still had to abide by a basic set of rules."},{"time":800000,"text":"This set off a cycle"},{"time":803000,"text":"of what we can call political innovation,"},{"time":805000,"text":"which led eventually to the idea of consent of the governed --"},{"time":808000,"text":"which was implemented for the first time"},{"time":811000,"text":"by that radical revolutionary government"},{"time":814000,"text":"in America across the pond."},{"time":817000,"text":"So now we need to figure out"},{"time":820000,"text":"how to build consent of the networked."}]},{"cues":[{"time":822000,"text":"And what does that look like?"},{"time":824000,"text":"At the moment, we still don't know."},{"time":827000,"text":"But it's going to require innovation"},{"time":831000,"text":"that's not only going to need"},{"time":834000,"text":"to focus on politics,"},{"time":836000,"text":"on geopolitics,"},{"time":838000,"text":"but it's also going to need"},{"time":840000,"text":"to deal with questions"},{"time":843000,"text":"of business management, investor behavior,"},{"time":846000,"text":"consumer choice"},{"time":848000,"text":"and even software design and engineering."},{"time":852000,"text":"Each and every one of us has a vital part to play"},{"time":855000,"text":"in building the kind of world"},{"time":858000,"text":"in which government and technology"},{"time":861000,"text":"serve the world's people and not the other way around."}]},{"cues":[{"time":864000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":866000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}